benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to account

covered: Empty Response: @TC15 covers removal of all custom fields with empty array
Request Body Validation: @TC10, @TC11, @TC18, @TC20, @TC21 cover malformed JSON, invalid objects, partial invalid objects

Edge Cases: @TC15 (empty array), @TC16 (max values), @TC17 (extra properties), @TC18 (partial objects), @TC19 (timeout), @TC20 (security injections), @TC21 (XSS), @TC22 (retry), @TC23 (duplicates), @TC24 (backward compatibility), @TC25 (concurrent requests), @TC26 (payload size), @TC27 (dependent service), @TC28 (external system), @TC29 (accessibility)
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination or chunked updates.
Authorization: No explicit tests for missing or invalid authentication tokens beyond @TC12.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios testing system behavior under high request volume or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for cache headers, ETag, or cache validation mechanisms.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling when large numbers of custom fields are involved.
Include explicit authorization tests, e.g., missing or invalid tokens, to verify security controls.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache validation behavior, such as ETag and Cache-Control.
